<TEXT>     Insurance Commissioner <PERSON>John Garamendi</PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION>First Capital Life</ORGANIZATION> is in
"hazardous condition," and said the increasing number of policy surrenders
threatens the company's long-term viability.;    The action comes about a
month after <LOCATION>California</LOCATION> and <LOCATION>New York</LOCATION> regulators seized the two main insurance
units of <ORGANIZATION>First Executive Corp.</ORGANIZATION>, which at the time had the industry's largest
